content: Never have I read a better, more creative story and the best thing is this is one of many
Amazing and breathtaking

Very well written: the different paths you could take depending on your choices were all very thought out and quite thought provoking. The story has left me pondering the future of advanced self-learning AI technology and what role it might play in our society and how we may have to adapt our policies and ethics to accommodate the progress. I found myself thoroughly engrossed for multiple readthroughs trying to discover the other paths/endings.

Amazing story with characters that feel like actual friends I actually learned some things about myself because of all the hard choices (for example you might want too use the robots to save humanity but would you sell out for 100 million dollars) my only complaint is that I feel like it could have been longer but it was already pretty long amazing story that I will never forget

This was the first CYOA novel I played and it's still where I'd recommend anyone should start. Quite short but the story can branch out in wildly different directions and you'll want to replay it at least a couple of times. It's very fun and a proper page-turner, but it does lack the emotional punch that some others have achieved (Choice of Rebels, Fallen Hero, Wayhaven etc). I also feel the endings don't *quite* live up to how the first half sparks your imagination. Still, highly recommend.

I love this book. The robots that I can create is so cool. I love that I can name my self and my robot cause it gives me a choice. I'm really glad that it was paid for me to play it. I recommend it. It was worth it. I can't wait to do the rest of the book. Keep making more books. When I download more and more of those ever day I look for mythical creature ones cause I like myths especially with unicorns. Just wish that the others were free.
Very beautiful game that will make you question what kind of person you will make yourself out to be.

The story begin with either a daunting nightmare or an unanswered questions, but as the character underwent the journey of each choices I made, It became more and more heart-wrenching, eye-opening and nerve-racking. Not all the choices are bad news, there's also an interesting scenes I discovered unintentionally which made the whole plot even more entertaining. This story definitely kept me company during this troubled times. Thumbs up to the developers team to produce such a good quality story.
Interesting and hails back to my computer science / AI days. Tech, labor, emotional angles. Warm hearted possibilities.
Very enjoyable. I only wish there was a save function in case mistakes are made.

This game....this story...I love it. I love how every choice has an effect whether you realize it or not. If it doesn't affect a stat, it affects humamity, relationships, wealth. I've played several times and certaon things always occur, but the fine details of it may change. Its rivetting and enjoyable and I recommend anyone play. One of the best purchases I've made.
An amazing piece of science fiction with an uncanny ability to make the reader feel be the character, no matter how many replays later. Definitely worth every cent and every second. :^)
Great game
Refund

The choices are weighty, and the emotions are richly written, while maintaining humor & frankness that won me over instantly. It's wildly replayable- I've played maybe 6 times already and it doesn't get old. I'm already thinking about seeing what I can do differently that I haven't already seen. My only complaint is, the game forces binary gender choices: my robot can be ungendered but I can't be, which sucks.

This was and still is my favorite game but I'm currently dying of frustration because a new update just came out which brutally destroys the controls. Swiping sideways on a choice now selects it, and it's really sensitive, which means that every time you put down you phone and your hand brushes against the screen or whatever (which should be allowed because this an essentially turn-based game that doesn't require quickly reacting to anything) you will unintentionally select a choice which could have major game-altering consequences and often requires resetting your entire save file and starting over to get back on track to what you were trying to do furthermore, to add insult to injury, every time you try to select a choice the normal way by tapping on it before hitting enter, the game plays an obnoxious animation advertising ruining any possibility of ignoring the thing to try to save myself the stress of thinking about it, and it blocks you from scrolling when you're touching a choice, which makes things really difficult when there's a long list of choices where you need to scroll to see them and not a lot of text to touch to navigate. There is no setting to opt out of this misery, and believe me, I check every three pages just in case. If I could bring myself to I would give this game one star just for this update. I can't, in honesty, because it really is an incredible game besides this part, but I seriously recommend you save yourself the endless frustration by waiting until this is fixed before you get invested in this game.

The working feels a bit rushed at places (especially in the second half of the game), most of the characters don't really have distinct voices and most of the relationships you build seem forced with unrealistic interactions. Again, it's not all bad, and the idea is very interesting but, especially after all the amazing reviews, I was expecting something so much more than what I got (also longer).

The story was intresting the AI story is not something that comes up much and i really enjoyed how ur choices really effected the stats a lot. HOWEVER it was way to rushed. Waaay to rushed and that took away a lot of fun for me. It kept me from being immersed in the story which is the entire reason i read these. Jumping that many years in that short of time made it feel really really short and because of that i fell i was over charged as well. It would have been better to break the time periods down i to different books making each time period a little more personally detailed. It was ok. Very interesting idea and as i said, i enjoyed the stats, but for the money, it could have been written better. Kepp trying!

Okay so if it wasn't obvious already, I wasn't happy with this interactive story. I wanted to like it. The genera was intriguing and I've always been interesting in the Robot and A.I. world. Being a creator of both was obviously going to make me happily get it. Along with the amazing reviews of previous players. I was easily able to look past the hefty price tag. It must be good right?  In some aspects, it was good. Written beautifully. Great punctuation and spelling. And the story idea was captivating. However my play through was somewhat disappointing. I felt it was rushed, way too rushed. If it was done in a longer, stretched out manner, the age difference from when you start to when you end wouldn't be a problem. However, aging from in your twenties to near fifties in under an hour is not fun.   This may be a metaphor for life or something. â€œLife flashes before your eye's, so  enjoy every moment of itâ€ is what I've concluded in my head. If this is so then I get it. But that is not what I want in a book. I wish to ESCAPE life when I read these interactive storiesâ€” or any book/game for that matter.  Have it been rushed I couldn't get close to any character, however I apparently did. How? I don't know it skipped that part. In the end I didn't find myself attached to anyone. The book didn't leave me thinking or emotionally damaged, just disappointed.   On the account of it being so short, this is an interactive story that is to be played multiple times. I just couldn't do it. If my first play through was less then impressive it clouds my decision to play again. I am not a multiple play through type of person. Especially when I doubt it's worth...  I'm not having a go at the Author. They have created a difficult thing and I applaud them for that. Just the fact that they got this out there is amazing. My problem is just how the story was set out. Like a full television season that has been trimmed down to a not-so-lengthy hour.    To conclude. If you are into multiple quick play through, and creating robots and A.I., then do not hesitate to buy. It is a good interactive story, if you don't mind the (quite) large plot skips.    Thank you Author and Choice Of Game's for this interactive story.   ~Blight

In most games and Choice of Games the character dies, you might replay it 4 or 5 times and the outcome barely changes from the 3 default endings made to make your choices feel "important". Not all CYOA games were bad, but this game...this game can barely be called a game. A game keeps you occupied, or just entertainment and eventualy you forget about it and life goes on. This...entity of creativity is so well written, it absolutely changed my way of thinking. The robot that you create, the thing you pour your soul into, just reading how it makes its way into the world as any number of things. This living embodiment of deep meaning, if looked at from a certain angle, just blows me away. After I played this, I was oblivious to how it can reach your core. Then I played again, and after I couldnt sit down. I was shaking, my mind being exposed to this concept of life I hadnt undersood before. I cant explain, its almost too much for me to comprehend, much less write down. This was the first CYOA book or game (if you must call it that) that i had played. This universe of diverse and deep choices, must be given a chance. I have so much more to say, but in the end, the story speaks for itself. Not everyone will understand it the way I do, but give it a shot. It might blow your mind

I would say the best way to describe Choice of Robots is an immersive experience. There is a veritable multitude of paths and choices to make, each creating a very unique and personable experience. Whether you are looking for a story of romance, war, business, or any combination of those factors and more, there is likely something for you here. My only complaint is that I wish my personal story could have gone on for even longer! Even if you do not already have much of an interest in robots, I would still give this story a try!
I've played this story dozens of times, and every time there's something new for me to read. I hope another five star review will help you if you're on the fence about buying this
Ugh I've played almost all of their games and this one is absolutely my favorite, the depth, characters and endings are absolutely awesome and it's so worth every penny (*'â–½'*)â™ª

One of the best choice games I've ever played. So much replay value and each story feels full and fleshed out (and not just the same story with slight, meaningless differences). Havn' t found anything that compares since I first played it years ago
Best choice of game. Would love more of this story. Perhaps a remaster with more features and story line. I dont know but I played this about 8 or 9 times now.
Very interesting story!

This was phenomenal! Choice of robots. I almost want to take away one of the stars because I can't find a sequel. However I can't bring myself to put down the best RPG I have ever experienced. I have played it 8 or so times... maybe more. I will continue to do so. I pretty much never give even 4 stars, but Choice of Robots deserves it. Thank You. Choice of Robots surpassed all the expectations I ever had for a CYOA game. What I mean to say is this: I had played a plenty of CYOAs before, but this masterpiece raised a bar higher than ever before. The story, characters, choices and interactivity - all of them combined in such a wonderful interactive reading experience.  This game got me immersed in its world and even more importantly, the game made me care for the characters and events that would occur. It resulted in making careful decisions and when I watched the story unfold, I was amazed by the complex design. Choice of Robots is one of the best CYOAs out there (on par with Tin Star), so for all the CYOA fans out there - try it out!

If you get yourself into a romantic, personal, or professional conflict, you're going to feel it. You will get deeply involved for the two or so hours it takes to complete the story. Totally worth the price!
Great text based game that offers so much variety upon playing that you could make only a few different changes during your playthroughs and end up in a completely different place. Brilliant.

Fantastic implementation of choice in this text based adventure. My first play through I made a character very much like myself - and being able to use my name and names I chose really helped draw me in! It was such a fantastic experience, and I'd recommend it to anyone.
Best choice of games story iv read so far.

It's so beautiful, a well written story. I got married, have child, a robot and her own created child, get through a sickness and get happy ending.. It kinda make me reluctant to play it again with different ending.
I really hope that in the future there will be more games like this, loved it.
Could tell the work put into this, with the many paths to take and the story really gets you, and have you want to continue and wonder what will happen next and carefully make your choses.

By far the best choice of game so far, I am not very very interested in robots and have played through the game like 50 times. Skipping the reading after the first playthrough because theres a lot of it.

Truly does justice to its genre as a "choose your own adventure" game. There are not only different endings, but the story actually changes depending on your decisions. I got to bang a robot 10/10

Extremely excellent game

In one life I was balancing the heart and the mind, trying to create an all around type of robot, but ended up alone and dying. In the next I chose to get married to my robot companion, contribute to society with medical robots, adopted a child that would be like a sibling to my first robot companion, while also being served by a robot butler. 10/10 would build Miku again.
OMG. The amount of replayability in this game is amaaaazing. Kudos to the author for making a well thought out and immerseful story! Gotta start a new playover now XD

Great

I'm a fan of the original "Choose your adventure" books so these type of games are perfect for me. If you really can't play a game without sound and graphics then pass this up but for anyone else it's well worth it.

Bought it on Steam also, and noticed the Steam version has some changes or extra options, such as choice of "programing software ie: GO, Java, Python, VisualC etc,"  The Stats / Results screen could be a little more informative giving you a better breakdown and info about your robot(s), upgrade history, etc. I do enjoy the chapter progression summary.

Here is a game with meaningfully responsive and well implemented moral choices, this time on a compellingly palpable near-future backdrop.  In every play through of the considerably branching story, I was consistently surprised by the depth and realism of game responses to my actions. Most importantly to me, every game ending felt appropriately earned, a reward to the player not every game in the genre can offer so satisfyingly. Highly recommended!  Many thanks to author Kevin Gold and all else jnvolved!

Choice Of Games continues to impress me with their style of interactive fiction. Imagine a game like Dragon Age or Mass Effect, but stripped of everything except interesting choices and satisfying long term consequences with no filler. Your choices build stats that determine how critical turning points play out, and you always feel like you earned whatever ending you found, whether it's an untimely death, a happily ever after, or something less clear cut in the middle.
Best Choice of Games I've played.  Lots of paths to choose from.

The branching paths are so diverse that it almost forces you to replay after the game ends. Good length too for an average run. Interesting that the subject of robots in every day life is something that is not far from real. Definitely made me think a lot. The variety of choices you can make and the range of changes they make in the world and characters of the story are impressive. This is easily one of my top 5 mobile games. Well worth the price, though it is shorter than some choice of games, the quality and replayability make up the difference.
